Why use pcoa?

We use PCoA because the inputs to adonis(), betadisper, etc are dissimilarity matrices and the aim is to show t hose dissimilarities (and the group centroids/dispersions) as best as possible whilst preserving the direct link to the distance values (ie why we don’t use NMDS). https://stat.ethz.ch/pipermail/r-sig-ecology/2013-August/004011.html
